node.text:
Danny at work profile testing for new coffees we're excited to release soon.
We hope that our seasonal rotation of coffees highlights only the best of a harvest, we work hard to achieve this!

@guilttripcoffee in Belfast have a selection of our seasonal coffees on their shelves! —— We're big fans of these guys and love working with Ben, Callum and co.
They are featuring our washed Biftu from Ethiopia and our extended fermentation La Montana from Guatemala.
Tasting of strawberry, dark chocolate and black tea. Farmed by Dagoberto and his eleven siblings, this is an exceptional coffee. —— Available now on our website! Photo, @stephenlister

We're really excited to announce the release of this natural Aguilera Naranjo from Costa Rica. It's one of the most complex acidities we've tasted in a long time.

We're roasting again tomorrow so be sure to order before 9pm tonight! Link in the bio. 
Photo, @stephenlister

Delighted to be featured by @sweetspotkaffee in Munich. It's been a pleasure to hear good things about our coffees from them and we think Markus and his team are doing wonders with Sweetspot. Be sure to stop by for a brew, you won't be disappointed.
We're roasting again tomorrow! Last few hours to get your orders in and we have new coffees available on both wholesale and retail websites. —— We can't get over how they're tasting!
We have two new coffees now available on our web store and wholesale. We're very impressed by these coffees and can't wait to share them with you! —— Photo, @murrayorr

Little Fitzroy — a strong community where a seasonal rotation of coffees is highly celebrated. Quality is considered in each cup.

It's always a pleasure to work with Cathryn and her team at Little Fitzroy, Easter Rd, Edinburgh. — photos, @stephenlister
We've had some very exciting coffees arrive at the roastery today and we're looking forward to releasing them next week. —— Keep your eyes peeled for more details! Photo, @murrayorr
We've been enjoying flavours like cranberry, pear, hazelnut and milk chocolate from this unique coffee, Las Colmenas. —— Available now for wholesale and retail, link in the bio!

Virgilio Mejia Membreño is the owner of Las Colmenas, a three hectare farm at 1300m in the Rio Colorado area of San Pedro, Copan. —— We have just a small amount of this beautiful coffee left, so be quick. Roasting again on Thursday for Friday dispatch.

Our weekly Wednesday quality assessment comprises of a selection on profiles from our previous production week and experimental test profiles. We examine each cup for consistency in body, acidity, sweetness, balance and more.

At the end of the process, we are left with reference profiles for each coffee, helping us maintain consistent quality in our roasting the next day.

Our good friend Jess from @27.elliotts elliotts has written a journal post on us at the roastery. We think it's brilliant and had a great time tasting coffees together! —— Go and give it a read and check out the other exciting content from 27 Elliotts. Click the link in our bio. — photo, @murrayorr

Ericka lets the coffee dry ferment for a longer period of time in controlled conditions in order to accentuate fruity characteristics in the cup.

Available now on our website.

La Montaña farmed by Ericka Sanchez in the San Antonio Huista area of Huehuetenango, Guatemala.

This is an exceptional example from Guatemala of a washed, organic extended fermentation coffee. Tasting of apples and blueberry bubblegum. Available to purchase on our website.
We're feeling great about 2020! Excited to work with brilliant coffees and share them with you all. —— photo, @murrayorr

That's us completed our last roasting session of the year!

We've worked with a large number of outstanding coffees this year and had the pleasure of roasting for many fantastic people running coffee spaces around the world. We are so thankful to you all!

We are so excited for 2020 with many new plans evolving, we can't wait to share them.

Sam, Alice and the team.

Photo, @stephenlister

The Free Company

Angus, Charlie and the team have been brewing our coffees out in Balerno at their seasonal dining series. Eating here is an incredible experience and a great way to taste some of the freshest Scottish ingredients grown on site. It's a pleasure to work with these guys on their coffee offering.

Photo, @murrayorr

We are working with a new coffee this week and it's a beautiful washed Honduran by Virgilio Mejia Membreño. The farm, Las Colmenas, is a three hectare farm at 1300 masl in the Rio Colorado area of San Pedro, Copan.

We've been enjoying tasting pear, hazelnut and cranberry flavours from this incredible red catuai variety.

It is available to purchase via our wholesale and retail webstores now.

Photo, @murrayorr

Christmas ordering dates — Our last roast day of the year is the 19th of Dec.

We're looking forward to roasting for your Christmas brewing, so be sure to place an order before the 19th!

Our next roast day will be the 8th of Jan. 
Photo, @stephenlister

Broken Clock — Pouring natural Mustafa Abakeno, Ethiopia.

Good friends Artem and Anna have created a beautiful space where coffees are represented very well and the quality of their baking is on par. 
Make it a visit when you're in West End Glasgow! —— photo, @murrayorr

Finca El Paraiso, Natural - Guatemala. We're really proud to be working with this natural from Stuardo Coto.

Since the mid 80's, Stuardo has invested in education and infrastructure to grow specialty coffee and his results this year are proved by this coffee, tasting of strawberries and honey.

We're sending this coffee out this week to @littlefitzroy in Edinburgh, @crtdktchn in Belfast, @slake.coffee in France and soon at a new opening in Wales... — photo, @stephenlister

BØLGE are brewing our coffees this weekend. We're excited to be featured by this coffee space in Slovakia. Matus and the team are working with a range of our coffees including natural Nuguse Mare, extended fermentation Todos Santos and washed Santa Teresa.

27 Elliotts — cooking local ingredients to create beautiful dishes paired with an honest coffee experience.

We're looking forward to working together on a different brewing approach in the near future.

Photo by @murrayorr

Subscription — We've selected this months subscription coffees and we're looking forward to sharing them with you! We have an incredible pre-release coffee included in this months subscription.
Shipping on Friday 22nd November. Link in bio to sign up.
